value.title: Biden is asked if he benefited from White privilege
value.excerpt: During a CNN town hall in Pennsylvania, Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden addresses how "the talk" within Black families about police interaction will be different under his administration, and if he believes he's benefited off White privilege.

value.title: READ: Judge's ruling criticizing Trump and DeJoy for USPS changes
value.excerpt: Federal Judge Stanley Bastian criticized President Donald Trump and Postmaster General Louis DeJoy and issued a nationwide order blocking some recent changes that slowed down mail services.

value.title: Trump rails against the 'liberal indoctrination of America's youth' in latest culture war salvo
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump railed against what he described as "the liberal indoctrination of America's youth" during a Constitution Day speech on Thursday, marking his latest attempt to inflame the culture wars raging in America ahead of the election.

value.title: Twitter public policy director decamps for Biden transition team
value.excerpt: Twitter public policy director Carlos Monje's exact position on the transition team was not immediately clear.

value.title: FBI Director Wray says Russia is actively interfering in 2020 election to 'denigrate' Biden
value.excerpt: FBI Director Christopher Wray said Thursday that Russia has been "very active" in its efforts to influence US elections, with the primary goal being to "denigrate" Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden.

value.title: Pennsylvania Supreme Court election rulings are big wins for Biden
value.excerpt: The Pennsylvania Supreme Court on Thursday removed the Green Party candidate from the 2020 presidential ballot and cleared the way for local officials to start sending out absentee ballots to voters.

value.title: Sen. Ron Johnson won't travel with Trump after exposure to individual who tested positive for Covid
value.excerpt: Republican Sen. Ron Johnson of Wisconsin will no longer be traveling with President Donald Trump on Thursday after learning that he was exposed to an individual who tested positive for Covid-19, a spokesman for the senator announced.

value.title: Biden tells Democratic senators he takes 'nothing for granted' during caucus call
value.excerpt: The Democratic presidential nominee called into the Senate Democrats’ daily caucus meeting Thursday and reassured members that he'll hit the trail in the final stretch of the campaign — particularly in key swing states.

value.title: GOP growing more indifferent with Trump controversies as election nears
value.excerpt: Public health experts reacted with alarm after President Donald Trump held an indoor rally with thousands of maskless supporters at a packed arena in Nevada amid the deadly coronavirus pandemic.

value.title: Businesses reject Trump payroll tax plan while postponing their own tax bills
value.excerpt: Most American workers won’t be getting the payroll tax break pushed by President Donald Trump, thanks to widespread opposition from employers. But many businesses are using a similar break to punt their own payroll tax bills. Tens of thousands of ...

value.title: Trump administration blocks some Xinjiang goods from China suspected of being made with slave labor
value.excerpt: The Trump administration issued new import restrictions on Monday against Chinese companies it accuses of using slave labor, including products from suspected mass prison camps in China's western Xinjiang region.

value.title: Biden proposes $5 trillion in new spending, undaunted by Trump's massive deficits
value.excerpt: The nation's deficits and outlays have hit post-World War II highs thanks to tax cuts under President Donald Trump, but Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden is proposing adding to that, at least in the near term, with a $5.4 trillion spending plan.

value.title: Down-ballot Dems split from Biden on door-knocking
value.excerpt: Amid growing anxiety about the loss of a valuable election-year tool, an increasing number of Democrats are ignoring Joe Biden’s lead and resuming traditional door-to-door canvassing.

value.title: Trump baselessly questions climate science during California wildfire briefing
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump on Monday baselessly asserted that climate change is not playing a role in the catastrophic wildfires overtaking forests across the west, rebutting an official briefing him who pleaded for the President listen to the science.

value.title: Republicans see Trump's rallies as his path to victory. Democrats welcome the events.
value.excerpt: The decision to hold a political rally has become one of the sharpest differences between the candidates in an election year defined by a global pandemic.

value.title: Trump and Biden both boast about creating auto industry jobs — but differ on how
value.excerpt: "I got you so many damn car plants,” President Trump told auto workers last week. Biden, meanwhile, is pledging "1 million new, well-paying jobs in the American automobile industry."

value.title: Fact check: Trump makes four false claims in one sentence
value.excerpt: In what may be a new record for President Donald Trump, he made four false claims in one sentence of a tweet on Saturday.

value.title: Court rules that Trump can end humanitarian protections for 300,000 immigrants
value.excerpt: A split federal appeals court panel said the Trump administration can terminate humanitarian protections for 300,000 immigrants from Sudan, Nicaragua, Haiti and El Salvador.

value.title: Top Trump Health Aide Attacks Scientists and Warns of Armed Revolt
value.excerpt: Michael Caputo, the assistant secretary of health for public affairs, told a Facebook audience without evidence that left-wing hit squads were being trained for insurrection, and he accused C.D.C. scientists of “sedition.

value.title: Joe Biden says US is facing 'one of the most difficult moments in our history'
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden said Monday that the United States is facing one of the most difficult moments in the nation's history, with "four historic crises all at the same time."

value.title: Pence cancels a plan to attend a fund-raiser hosted by QAnon supporters.
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence has called off plans to attend a fund-raiser in Bozeman, Mont., on Monday evening hosted by a couple who have shown support for QAnon, the convoluted conspiracy theory built around the notion of a deep-state cabal of Satan-worshiping pedophiles and their powerful Democratic backers.

value.title: Biden campaign readies massive legal team for voting, election issues
value.excerpt: Joe Biden's campaign has assembled an extensive legal team to focus on voting and election issues.

value.title: Michael Cohen's daughter says she was taken aback by Trump's behavior toward her father
value.excerpt: Samantha Cohen, the daughter of President Donald Trump's former lawyer, says she was taken aback by his behavior toward her father during a 2012 incident in which her father says Trump leered at her.

value.title: There Are Dozens of Kenoshas, and Joe Biden Needs to Speak to All of Them
value.excerpt: Neglected cities across this country are desperate for a sincere and savvy politics of racial and economic justice.

value.title: Trump ignores science at dangerous indoor rally
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump offered a glaring new example of his refusal to put medical science before politics with a large indoor rally Sunday night that made a mockery of social distancing, while the pandemic he mismanaged has now claimed more than 194,000 American lives.

value.title: Biden campaign grows more diverse with people of color making up nearly half of staff
value.excerpt: Joe Biden's presidential campaign grew more diverse in its staffing over the summer months with people of color now making up nearly half of the campaign's full-time staff and women on the campaign growing in their majority.

value.title: L.A. mayor: ‘Instead of hitting the golf course,’ Trump and Congress should ensure wildfire aid
value.excerpt: He is going to come out here and probably tell us, ‘I'm going to send you rakes instead of more help,’” Garcetti said on CNN.

value.title: Trump finally releases controversial drug price executive order
value.excerpt: More than seven weeks after President Donald Trump signed four executive orders aimed at lowering drug prices, the White House finally released Sunday perhaps the most controversial one.

value.title: Trump unveils plan to slash drug costs tied to what's paid abroad
value.excerpt: The plan would tie payments for certain Medicare drugs to the significantly lower costs the treatments sell for abroad.

value.title: Mormons rejected Trump as blasphemous. Now he likely can’t win without them.
value.excerpt: Mormons rejected Donald Trump in numbers unheard of for a Republican nominee — viewing the thrice-married, immigrant-bashing Republican as an affront to their values.
